    • hasContentType

      public boolean hasContentType(String... contentTypes)
      Tells whether or not the HTTP header contains any of the given Content-Type values.

      The values are expected to be in lower case.

      Parameters:

      Returns:
      true if any of the given values is contained in the (first) Content-Type header, false otherwise.
      Since:
      2.8.0

    • getNormalisedContentTypeValue

      public String getNormalisedContentTypeValue()

      The normalisation is done by changing all characters to lower case.

      the value normalised, might be null.
      Since:

      public String getHeadersAsString()

    • isEmpty

      public boolean isEmpty()
      Tells whether or not the header is empty.

      true if the header is empty, false otherwise.
